The cooperative model assumes that the target is regulated by a complex of HrdB and RbpA. This is a slight extension of the direct model and it is a novel contribution of this paper. The model follows Equation 2, but the HrdB + RbpA complex is considered as a regulator (y). The concentration of the complex is in turn determined by the concentrations of its constituents and an equilibrium constant q:
(3)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
